		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Here's how I understand it:
<br /><ul><li>Iff a bin has water in it, the function is true when <em>a</em> is false and <em>b</em> is false. </li><li>Iff a bin has apple in it, the function is true when <em>a</em> is true and <em>b</em> is false. </li><li>Iff a bin has orange in it, the function is true when <em>a</em> is false and <em>b</em> is true. </li><li>Iff a bin has plum in it, the function is true when <em>a</em> is true and <em>b</em> is true.  </li></ul>For example, function "a OR b":<br /><ul><li><em>a</em> false, <em>b</em> false: result false, no water </li><li><em>a</em> true, <em>b</em> false: result true, apple </li><li><em>a</em> false, <em>b</em> true: result true, orange </li><li><em>a</em> true, <em>b</em> true: result true, plum </li></ul>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
